t time to prevent.</p>","updated":1618060403,"_links":{"self":{"href":"https://api.tvmaze.com/shows/1759"},"previousepisode":{"href":"https://api.tvmaze.com/episodes/152710"}}},{"id":1760,"url":"https://www.tvmaze.com/shows/1760/anne-of-green-gables","name":"Anne of Green Gables","type":"Scripted","language":"English","genres":["Drama","Family"],"status":"Ended","runtime":120,"premiered":"1985-12-05","officialSite":null,"schedule":{"time":"","days":["Sunday"]},"rating":{"average":8.5},"weight":0,"network":{"id":36,"name":"CBC","country":{"name":"Canada","code":"CA","timezone":"America/Halifax"}},"webChannel":null,"dvdCountry":null,"externals":{"tvrage":14367,"thetvdb":81954,"imdb":"tt0088727"},"image":{"medium":"https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_portrait/9/24599.jpg","original":"https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/original_untouched/9/24599.jpg"},"summary":"<p>One hundred years ago, Anne of Green Gables introduced readers to one of the most enduring characters in fiction and launched Canada's most lucrative literary franchise. The heartwarming story of the plucky red-headed orphan has gone on to sell hundreds of millions of copies and become the basis for an unprecedented television phenomenon. But behind the fictional and feisty Anne Shirley lurked the often-tormented life of author Lucy Maud Montgomery. CBC Archives takes a look at the life, death and lasting legacy of the woman who created Anne.</p>","updated":1606272023,"_links":{"self":{"href":"https://api.tvmaze.com/shows/1760"},"previousepisode":{"href":"https://api.tvmaze.com/episodes/1753379"}}},{"id":1761,"url":"https://www.tvmaze.com/shows/1761/anne-of-green-gables","name":"Anne of Green Gables","type":"Animation","language":"Japanese","genres":["Drama","Anime"],"status":"Ended","runtime":25,"premiered":"1979-01-07","officialSite":null,"schedule":{"time":"19:30","days":["Sunday"]},"rating":{"average":null},"weight":53,"network":{"id":131,"name":"Fuji TV","country":{"name":"Japan","code":"JP","timezone":"Asia/Tokyo"}},"webChannel":null,"dvdCountry":null,"externals":{"tvrage":31907,"thetvdb":84569,"imdb":"tt0078560"},"image":{"medium":"https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_portrait/9/24689.jpg","original":"https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/original_untouched/9/24689.jpg"},"summary":"<p><b>Anne of Green Gables</b> is an animated television series, part of Nippon Animation's World Masterpiece Theater. It was adapted from the novel, Anne of Green Gables, by Lucy Maud Montgomery. Produced by Nippon Animation in 1979, it was first broadcast on Fuji TV from January 7, 1979 to December 30, 1979. Fifty episodes were produced in total.</p><p>It has been exported to neighbouring Asian countries and also to Europe and Canada. As with the novels, the animated version of Anne is much beloved in Japan to this day and \"DVD memorial BOX set\" was released on August 22, 2008 and a new anime series that serves as a prequel to the series, Kon'nichiwa Anne 〜 Before Green Gables, which premiered on April 5, 2009 in Japan.</p>","updated":1582066879,"_links":{"self":{"href":"https://api.tvmaze.com/shows/1761"},"previousepisode":{"href":"https://api.tvmaze.com/episodes/152762"}}},{"id":1762,"url":"https://www.tvmaze.com/shows/1762/the-adventures-of-tom-sawyer","name":"The Adventures of Tom Sawyer","type":"Animation","language":"Japanese","genres":["Drama","Adventure"],"status":"Ended","runtime":25,"premiered":"1980-01-06","officialSite":null,"schedule":{"time":"","days":[]},"rating":{"average":8.3},"weight":53,"network":{"id":131,"name":"Fuji TV","country":{"name":"Japan","code":"JP","timezone":"Asia/Tokyo"}},"webChannel":null,"dvdCountry":null,"externals":{"tvrage":null,"thetvdb":80944,"imdb":"tt0168391"},"image":{"medium":"https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_portrait/9/24770.jpg","original":"https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/original_untouched/9/24770.jpg"},"summary":"<p><i><b>The Adventures of Tom Sawyer</b></i> (トム・ソーヤーの冒険 <i>Tomu Sōyā no Bōken</i><b>?</b>) is a Japanese anime series, directed byHiroshi Saitô which was aired in 1980. It is based on the well-known and popular novel <i>The Adventures of Tom Sawyer</i>by Mark Twain.</p><p>The series was broadcast on the World Masterpiece Theater, an animation staple on Fuji TV that showcased each year an animated version of a different classical book or story of Western literature, and was originally titled \"Tom Sawyer no Bōken\". It was the second installment of the series, after 1977's <i>Rascal the Raccoon</i>, to feature the work of an American author.</p><p>This series was also dubbed to English by Saban International and aired on HBO circa 1988 under the title \"The Adventures of Tom Sawyer.\" It aired during the 7:30AM time slot and alternated with the later <i>WMT</i> version of \"Little Women.\" Celebrity Home Entertainment released videos in the United States under the title \"All New Adventures of Tom Sawyer\".</p><p>In 1997, 2008, 2010, and 2014, it was aired on ABS-CBN in the Philippines.</p><p>As of January 2011, the anime is airing in the United States (in the original Japanese) on the NHK's cable channel TV Japan.</p>","updated":1573321863,"_links":{"self":{"href":"https://api.tvmaze.com/shows/1762"},"previousepisode":{"href":"https://api.tvmaze.com/episodes/152949"}}},{"id":1763,"url":"https://www.tvmaze.com/shows/1763/el-ministerio-del-tiempo","name":"El Ministerio del Tiempo","type":"Scripted","language":"Spanish","genres":["Adventure","Science-Fiction"],"status":"Running","runtime":70,"premiered":"2015-02-24","officialSite":"http://www.rtve.es/television/ministerio-del-tiempo/","schedule":{"time":"22:40","days":["Wednesday"]},"rating":{"average":7.9},"weight":86,"network":{"id":146,"name":"La 1","country":{"name":"Spain","code":"ES","timezone":"Europe/Madrid"}},"webChannel":null,"dvdCountry":null,"externals":{"tvrage":47937,"thetvdb":292262,"imdb":"tt4136774"},"image":{"medium":"https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium