 with two by-the-book agents to battle global menaces.</p>","updated":1620065462,"_links":{"self":{"href":"https://api.tvmaze.com/shows/1891"},"previousepisode":{"href":"https://api.tvmaze.com/episodes/157659"}}},{"id":1892,"url":"https://www.tvmaze.com/shows/1892/sledge-hammer","name":"Sledge Hammer","type":"Scripted","language":"English","genres":["Comedy","Action"],"status":"Ended","runtime":30,"averageRuntime":30,"premiered":"1986-09-23","officialSite":null,"schedule":{"time":"21:30","days":["Friday"]},"rating":{"average":7.7},"weight":46,"network":{"id":3,"name":"ABC","country":{"name":"United States","code":"US","timezone":"America/New_York"}},"webChannel":null,"dvdCountry":null,"externals":{"tvrage":5220,"thetvdb":79170,"imdb":"tt0090525"},"image":{"medium":"https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_portrait/11/27611.jpg","original":"https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/original_untouched/11/27611.jpg"},"summary":"<p>Meet Inspector <b>Sledge Hammer</b>, a new kind of hero who makes Rambo look like Pee Wee Herman. Sledge is the trigger-happy lawman whose hatred of criminal scum and yogurt eatin' creeps was matched only by his love of excessive force and a .44 Magnum. Over the next two seasons, this hilariously deranged lampoon of Dirty Harry and plenty of other targets became one of the most notorious series in television history and launched a rabid cult of fans that grows to this day.</p>","updated":1619236747,"_links":{"self":{"href":"https://api.tvmaze.com/shows/1892"},"previousepisode":{"href":"https://api.tvmaze.com/episodes/157700"}}},{"id":1893,"url":"https://www.tvmaze.com/shows/1893/silk-stalkings","name":"Silk Stalkings","type":"Scripted","language":"English","genres":["Drama","Action","Crime"],"status":"Ended","runtime":60,"averageRuntime":60,"premiered":"1991-11-07","officialSite":null,"schedule":{"time":"","days":["Sunday"]},"rating":{"average":7},"weight":8,"network":{"id":30,"name":"USA Network","country":{"name":"United States","code